dcterms:description: A dataset of trigger infected models for classifying images from the MNIST dataset, generated by inserting two types of triggers into each image of the clean MNIST dataset.
dcterms:title: Triggered MNIST Dataset

dcterms:description: The NIST-Round0 dataset consists of CNN classification models for traffic sign signals, with half benign and half Trojaned models trained on synthetically created images of artificial traffic signs.
dcterms:title: NIST-Round0

dcterms:description: The NIST-Round1 dataset is similar to Round0 but consists of 1,000 models instead of 200, also containing both benign and Trojaned models trained on synthetic traffic sign images.
dcterms:title: NIST-Round1
